NAME
    add-to-path

DESCRIPTION
    Add a directory to your global PATH environment variable.

AVAILABLE PARAMETERS:
    $1 - path_dir       [The full directory path.]

SYNOPSIS
    add-to-path path_dir [--prepend,-p,-b || --save,-s || --verbose,-v]

EXAMPLES
    add-to-path --help
    add-to-path --prepend /home/user/bin
    add-to-path -v /usr/mybin
    add-to-path /usr/mybin --save

AVAILABLE OPTIONS
    -h, --help          [show this help documentation.]
    -p, -b, --prepend   [prepend to beginning of $PATH instead of the end.]
    -s, --save          [wether to save this new path permanetly, adding it to your shell rc file.]
    -v, --verbose       [Show detailed output.]
